A great result for our farmers and for our rural communities. - John, #FonterraResults

Strong outlook for this year.
A Forecast Farmgate Milk Price of $6.75 and earnings Per Share range of 45-55 cents - John, #FonterraResults
Our Gearing Ratio has remained stable at 44.3% due to higher equity offsetting impact of higher debt. - Paul, #FonterraResults
We have a solid performance across all our markets, with most led by Greater China, up 46%. - Paul, #FonterraResults
Our Foodservice business has increased volume by 12% in the last 12 months - Paul, #FonterraResults
Our CAPEX is down 10% to 851M with working capital down 2 days to 75 days in total. - Paul, #FonterraResults
We continue to reduce our OPEX from 8% last year to 6% this year. - Paul, #FonterraResults
We are looking to expand our milk supply & capacity, we will be looking to make further investments to meet demand - Theo, #FonterraResults
Our Australia re-set is now finished, it didn't happen overnight but we're heading in the right direction. - Theo, #FonterraResults
All and all, it is still a strong key strategic investment for us. Both in infant formula but also for China overall - Theo #FonterraResults
Both Beingmate and Anmum are registered, last year brands which weren't registered were impacted. - Theo, #FonterraResults

Fonterra business in China  –
Ingredients ~20% of vol, 1/5 share of Ingredients’ $1b profit of our global business - Theo, #FonterraResults

Advanced Ingredients segment – newly defined, but a core part of business,
Increased by over 470m LME. -Theo, #FonterraResults
Overall growing share of volume in higher value. Over 1b LME into higher value this year. -Theo, #FonterraResults
Our Foodservice business has a 47.2% return on capital, with a normalised EBIT of $614M. - Theo, #FonterraResults
Volume is down, and inventory is lowest ever.  But we're still up by milk price of 57% - Theo, #FonterraResults
We're investing in technology, and the digital world and in our people. - Theo, #FonterraResults
We have a demand-driven strategy, not a supply-driven. We shift as much as we can to higher value. - Theo, #FonterraResults
There is around a $0.10 cent benefit to our farmers, which is significant when you're a young farmer starting off. - John #FonterraResults
it's not just about the milk price, but Farm Source and the value and servive we provide our farmers. - John, #FonterraResults
2016/17 milk price is competitive when benchmarked around the world, - John #FonterraResults

Our absolute priority is to get cashflow to our farmers, we're currently ahead of target to get this to our farmers - John
Re: DIRA: whilst we're supportive of the legislation, we believe that it was set 16 years ago and doesn't fit our current state. - John
Australia, the biggest improvement is in Ingredients and our consumer business is doing well after our transformation. - Theo
Our focus is always to leave the environment better than we found it. - John
In regards to sustainability and water, there wouldn't be a farmer who doesn't have this front of mind, and we commend their efforts. - John
With our two farms in China, we're continuing to see an increase in volume, which allows us to pull more value - Lukas.
If you have big events in supply and demand, there will be volatility - it's not nice but it's the reality. - Theo
Volatility remains due to supply and demand, only 8% is globally traded. With geopolitical events having the biggest effect - Theo
There are some wonderful stories that are out there, which have been told and need to be told. It's good to be able to share them - John
It's pleasing to see our balance sheet continue to strengthen, and see our farmers and communities continue to benefit. - John
It is important for us to be able to maintain the forecast at $6.00 kg/MS however we know our farmers will remain cautious. - John
We targeting full year dividend of 40 cents per share and cash payout of $6.40 - John
Our Gearing ratio down which is  great result and we're on-track for 40-45 per cent at end of year. - Lukas
In our regions, Greater China and Oceania continuing to drive profits with China up 32%. - Lukas
Consumer and Foodservice has grown along our expectation, and EBIT is up 30% for the first half - Lukas
Despite our Ingredients are lower, we've still managed to achieve a $510 million EBIT. - Lukas
We're excited to have Disrupt take place globally this year, and there has been lots of interest from our people - Theo
Despite market conditions in China, our Anmum brand continues to grow in the market. - Theo
227 milion more LMEs into higher value categories including a further investment in a $240m mozzarella plant at Clandeboye - Theo
Ingredients are down due to lower milk volumes, however Foodservice and consumer continues to grow by 17%. - Theo

Strong performance across our Co-op despite lower milk volumes
Revenue up 5% to $9.2 billion
NPAT of $418 million up two per cent - Theo
Changes, we'll try to take as opportunities as we're strong. We'll continue to invest in our communities - Theo.
Global context, overall a very strong outlook for dairy. Alot is going to happen, a lot is going to change. -Theo
